title: The Grateful Dead Live at Rainbow Theater on 1981-03-21
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Tennessee Jed-> Little Red Rooster, Althea, Let It Grow-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Jack Straw, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> One More Saturday Night, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: Nice Matrix, Great Show I previously had the soundboard for this show and downloaded this to see how it compared and to my surprise this matrix was an improvement in the sound and listening experience.  As for the show, this and 3-28-81 are my favorite 2 shows of the spring Europe tour.  Althea, China-Rider and Let it Grow are all stand outs.  The 2nd set is also very well played.

Well-freakin'-done Outstanding work on this matrix. The AUD is just enough to give it that extra depth lacking in the SBD.  Spring 81 was a great run and this is an outstanding example.  Upbeat and hopping right out of the gate.  I think I can even hear Rob showing his appreciation.  Thanks for the effort on this one.
extraordinay show and matrix Wow.  The Let It Grow > China Cat > Rider is incredible.  I think the ChinaRiders from this month are better than just about any, except maybe June-August 1974.
Bloody fantastic Absolutely KILLER version of Eyes. The web Jerry weaves is majestic. An awesome show all around!

Other side of the pond Had SBD of this years back on cassette..played the living shit out of it..Must say that I like this matrix much better..the mix is perfect and you feel like your right there in the moment..I really like the song selection of this show..everything is upbeat,tight and well played..For me in the 1st set Peggy-0 stands out along with a powerful Let It Grow>China>Rider..Boom Shacka Lacka!!!! It carries over into the 2nd set With and interesting start with Jack Straw followed by Ship Of Fools then a wonderful Estimated>Eyes..Solid through to the encore..so please GIVE IT A WHIRL
Let it grow>China-Rider! Yes indeed! My-O-My
